					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12280243#post-4334092</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12280243/scared-stiff#post-4334092</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 18 Aug 2019 22:27:54 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zzuxon</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1496981</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm really digging Parawatch so far, but this may be my favorite. It makes excellent use of the Foundation-verse, without compromising Parawatch's signature separation from the veil. Using a Goosebumps-esque children's book series as a focus is VERY old-school creepypasta, but the use of the Anafabula makes this an authentically SCP work, makes loads of sense, fits perfectly with the Candle Cove-esque premise of the story, and made me feel smart for figuring out what was happening early on in the work. Really top notch work here.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12280243#post-4326244</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12280243/scared-stiff#post-4326244</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 09 Aug 2019 13:33:31 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>3146689</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I've had some conflicting feelings about this. In short, I think the beginning does its job fine, but the effects that follow (like the books predicting/causing bad events) follow pretty ordinary tropes. The part that was supposed to lure me into false sense of safety before the punchline didn't work that well either, it was pretty obvious what its purpose was and that the ending was approaching. Regarding the ending itself: I think it's pretty creative, but it didn't hit me that hard. Maybe I just didn't get all the implications that came with it, since sometimes I don't read into things enough.</p> <p>So, I've decided to stick with novote.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
